    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800 - INSTALL - STEERING COLUMN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the steering column shaft has been removed from the steering column housing:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">At the steering column housing lower end it is important that the lower flat washers,
                    spring, washer and bushing are installed properly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501012">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501012" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501012" filename="../figg05/G0501012.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Lower Steering Column Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. RETAINING RING</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. PUSH-ON NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. FLAT WASHERS</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. SPRING</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. BEARING</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">The upper bushings and washer must be properly installed (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501013">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0501013" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0501013" filename="../figg05/G0501013.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Upper Steering Column Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. BUSHING</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BEARING</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the steering column with shaft and slip yoke, and steering column bracket in place and
                connect the steering column U-joint to the steering gear. Tighten the pinch bolt as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_19.xml" xrefid="hl0501001">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl0501001"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the steering column bracket on the floor and tighten the four bolts as specified in
                the
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_19.xml" xrefid="hl0501001">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl0501001"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the four (4) steering column housing retaining bolts. Tighten as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_19.xml" xrefid="hl0501001">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl0501001"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect the air hoses to the trailer brake valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect the turn signal harness at the connector (
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_6.xml" xrefid="f0501008">Figure 8, Item 3</hotlnk>). Connect the horn wire to
                the connector (
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_6.xml" xrefid="f0501008">Figure 8, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the steering column housing cover, screws and washers. Tighten as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_19.xml" xrefid="hl0501001">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl0501001"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, install the steering wheel as described in
                <hotlnk document="s05010t_12.xml" xrefid="hl0501002">INSTALL, STEERING WHEEL
                    <xref refid="hl0501002"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
